Comments: 
        PlayerWithTwoSprites is looking much better now since last sprint. The
        readability as a result has also improved heavily.
        
        In PlayerInputBuffer I noticed that most of the ConsumeXY methods are very similar. This leads me to ask if they could be condensed into a single Consume method that takes in the vector as a reference and modifies it from there.

        I like the addition of a Config file for player to host all the numbers for the stats. I see that you are pulling from it in PlayerWithTwoSprites by that name in a string. This could probably moved to the top as a variable so that in the future, if we want to create instances of the player with different base stats, it is easier to modify.

        The PlayerTwoStatesManager is a definite good addition for understandability and division of responsibilities.

        The StatusEffectManager looks very nice. In AddEffect, however, it looks like the effect, after being merged, gets removed before it can be applied. Let me know if I have this mixed up.

        The implementations of the states also look good as a whole. The majority of them do look very similar so I would think about making an abstract class doing the math work and having each stat-specific implementation then use that math. This might shorten the amount of work each specific class does. Even if you choose to not use that exact architecture then I think something with that idea could be useful.